public abstract class BaseChannelHolder
extends BaseLocus
implements ChatChannelHolder

This is an abstract base class that provides a lot of what all ChatChannelHolder implementors need.

Author:
Dan Bornstein, danfuzz@milk.com

getKnownChannel

public final ChatChannel getKnownChannel(java.lang.String name)
Given a canonical name, return the known channel that corresponds to that name, or return null if there is no known channel with that name. No querying of the host should be done to satisfy this request.

Specified by:
getKnownChannel in interface ChatChannelHolder
Parameters:
name - the canonical channel name to look up
Returns:

updateChannels

public abstract void updateChannels()
Ask for the list of channels for this object to be updated from the host. Subclasses must override this method to do something appropriate. In particular, they should arrange for calls to addChannel(), removeChannel(), and/or setChannels() to happen, preferably asynchronously to the actual call to this method.

Specified by:
updateChannels in interface ChatChannelHolder

channelAdded

protected void channelAdded(ChatChannel channel)
BaseChannelHolder calls this method when a channel has been added. By default, it does nothing, but subclasses may want to override this to perform appropriate housekeeping. If this method is in fact overridden, subclasses should make sure to call super.channelAdded() to make sure all the superclasses get a chance to do their respective things.

Parameters:
channel - the channel that was added

addChannel

protected final void addChannel(ChatChannel channel)
Add a new channel to this object. This will automatically send out the right events to the right listeners. Also, if the target identity of this object is also a BaseChannelHolder and this object isn't its own target identity, then the identity will be informed of the given channel's existence. If null is passed, it is silently ignored.

Parameters:
channel - null-ok; the channel to add

removeChannel

protected final void removeChannel(ChatChannel channel)
Remove a channel from this object. This will automatically send out the right events to the right listeners. If null is passed, it is silently ignored.

Parameters:
channel - null-ok; the channel to remove

setChannels

protected final void setChannels(ChatChannel[] channels)

Parameters:
channels - null-ok; the new channel list

uberListenerAddedToChannels

protected final void uberListenerAddedToChannels(java.util.EventListener listener)
Tell all the channels in this object that an uber-listener was added to them. BaseChannelHolder.uberListenerAdded() doesn't do this automatically since some subclasses won't want that to happen. In particular, BaseUser does not want to tell its channels when an uber-listener is added. Note that channels only get informed if they are in fact subclasses of BaseEntity.

Parameters:
listener - the listener that was added
